2 (13)(a) (13) The Legislature finds and declares that:
3 (i) There there exists in this state a pressing need to attract and
4 retain qualified and dedicated public school employees and that one of
5 the factors prospective public school employees consider when seeking or
6 continuing public school employment is the retirement system and benefits
7 the employment provides; .
8 (ii) Over The Legislature further finds that over the past decades,
9 as reflected by the Medical Price Index published by the United States
10 Department of Labor, the cost of medical care, including the cost of
11 medications and insurance coverages, has increased at a rate in excess of
12 that by which the Consumer Price Index - All Urban Consumers has
13 increased; and .
14 (iii) There The Legislature further finds and declares that there
15 accordingly exists a need to adjust the amount of retirement benefits
16 paid to retired public school employees in order to assist them in
17 meeting the increased cost of medical care.
18 (b) Therefor, in addition to the cost-of-living adjustments provided
19 in subsections (1) through (12) of this section: ,
20 (i) Commencing commencing on October 3, 2001, and on October 3 of
21 every year thereafter until cost-of-living adjustments under subdivision
22 (13)(b)(ii) of this section apply, a medical cost-of-living adjustment
23 shall be paid to any annuitant who became a member prior to July 1, 2016,
24 and has been paid an annuity from the retirement system for at least ten
25 years through the October 3 adjustment date.
26 (ii) On September 1, 2026, and on September 1 of every year
27 thereafter, a medical cost-of-living adjustment shall be paid to any
28 annuitant who became a member prior to July 1, 2016, and has been paid an
29 annuity from the retirement system for at least ten years through the
30 September 1 adjustment date.
31 (c)(i) The medical cost-of-living adjustment shall be paid in the
-74-

