2026 2026
1 form of a supplemental annuity providing monthly payments equal to the
2 amount that which results when (A) (a) the fraction, not to exceed one,
3 that results when the annuitant's years of creditable service at his or
4 her retirement date is divided by twenty, is multiplied by (B) (b) the
5 product of ten dollars times the number of years, including attained one-
6 half years, that such annuitant has received annuity payments from the
7 retirement system through the medical cost-of-living October 3 adjustment
8 date.
9 (ii) The supplemental annuity being paid to an annuitant shall
10 increase by ten dollars on the medical cost-of-living adjustment date
11 October 3 of each subsequent year to reflect the additional year of
12 annuity payments to the annuitant until the total amount of the
13 supplemental annuity is two hundred fifty dollars.
14 (iii) In no event shall the medical cost-of-living adjustment for
15 any annuitant pursuant to this subsection result in the payment of a
16 supplemental annuity exceeding two hundred fifty dollars per month.
17 (d) The supplemental annuity paid to an annuitant pursuant to this
18 subsection shall cease at the death of the annuitant regardless of the
19 form of retirement annuity being paid to the annuitant at the time of his
20 or her death.
