26 amended to read:
27 81-2041 (1) Any officer who became a member prior to July 1, 2016,
28 and who meets the participation requirements of subsection (2) of this
29 section may participate in DROP. DROP provides that subsequent to
30 attaining normal age and service retirement eligibility, a member may
31 voluntarily choose to participate in DROP upon its adoption which, for
-91-

LB820 LB820
2026 2026
1 purposes of this section, shall be the earlier of September 1, 2008, or
2 the first of the month following a favorable letter determination by the
3 Internal Revenue Service. If the member chooses to participate in DROP,
4 the member shall be deemed to have retired but shall not be deemed to be
5 terminated, and the member may continue in active employment for up to a
6 five-year period. During the DROP period, the member's retirement benefit
7 payments shall be deposited into the DROP account for the benefit of the
8 member until the member actually retires from active employment at or
9 before the expiration of the DROP period. Thereafter, future retirement
10 benefit payments shall be made directly to the member, and the member
11 shall have access to all funds in the DROP account designated for the
12 benefit of the member. DROP funds shall be held and invested in a defined
13 contribution account under section 414(k) of the Internal Revenue Code
14 and shall meet the limitations in section 415 of the code.
15 (2) To participate in the DROP program, a member shall meet the
16 following requirements:
17 (a) A member shall be eligible to enter DROP at any time subsequent
18 to the date when the member has (i) attained normal retirement age and
19 (ii) completed twenty-five years of service. Members having attained
20 normal retirement age and completed twenty-five years of service on or
21 before the date of adoption of DROP shall be eligible to enter DROP at
22 any future date;
23 (b) A member who elects to enter DROP shall be entitled to receive
24 regular age and service retirement benefits in accordance with section
25 81-2026. A member is entitled to remain in DROP for a maximum of five
26 years subsequent to the date of the member's DROP election. A member may
27 separate from service and thereby exit DROP at any time during the DROP
28 period. On or before the completion of the DROP period, the member must
29 separate from active employment and exit DROP. During the DROP period, a
30 member's retirement benefit shall be payable to the DROP account vendor
31 designated in the member's name. Amounts transferred or paid to a
-92-

LB820 LB820
2026 2026
1 participating member's DROP account shall not constitute annual additions
2 under section 415 of the Internal Revenue Code;
3 (c) A member electing to enter DROP shall choose an annuity payment
4 option. After the option is chosen, the member shall not be entitled to
5 any retirement benefit changes, for reasons including, but not limited
6 to, wage increases, promotions, and demotions, except that the
7 restriction on retirement benefit changes shall not apply in the event of
8 duty-related death or duty-related disability. The benefit amount shall
9 be fixed as of the date of election and shall be payable as if the
10 employee retired on that date and separated from active employment. Upon
11 the death of a member during the DROP period, monthly benefits shall be
12 provided as a percentage of the amount of the member's annuity as set
13 forth in subsection (3) of section 81-2026 based upon the annuity benefit
14 calculation made at commencement of the DROP period. In addition, the
15 balance of the DROP account, if any, shall be provided to the beneficiary
16 or beneficiaries of the member in accordance with subsection (6) of
17 section 81-2026 or, if no beneficiary is provided, to the estate of the
18 member. Upon the disability of a member during the DROP period, the
19 member shall be deemed to have completed the DROP period, shall begin
20 receiving the annuity benefit as calculated at the commencement of the
21 DROP period, and shall be paid the balance of the DROP account, if any;
22 (d) No member shall be allowed to continue making the required
23 contributions while the member is enrolled in DROP;
24 (e) During the DROP period, the Nebraska State Patrol shall not be
25 assessed the amount required under subsection (2) of section 81-2017 nor
26 shall such amount be credited to the State Patrol Retirement Fund;
27 (f) The member shall be paid the balance of the DROP account upon
28 the member's separation from active employment or at the expiration of
29 the DROP period thereby ending the member's participation in DROP. If a
30 member has not voluntarily separated from active employment on or before
31 the completion of the DROP period, the member's retirement benefit shall
-93-

LB820 LB820
2026 2026
1 be paid directly to the member thereby ending the member's active
2 employment. The member's DROP account shall consist of accrued retirement
3 benefits and interest on such benefits;
4 (g) Any member that is enrolled in DROP shall be responsible for
5 directing the DROP account designated for the benefit of the member by
6 investing the account in any DROP investment options. There shall be no
7 guaranteed rate of investment return on DROP account assets. Any losses,
8 charges, or expenses incurred by the participating DROP member in such
9 member's DROP account by virtue of the investment options selected by the
