16 individual and any other amount credited on behalf of such individual by
17 the Legislative Council shall not exceed the total compensation to be
18 received by the individual from the employer or exceed the limits
19 established by the Internal Revenue Code for such a plan.
20 (3) The deferred compensation program shall serve in addition to but
21 not be a part of any existing retirement or pension system provided for
22 state or county employees or any other benefit program.
23 (4) Any compensation deferred at the election of the individual
24 under such a deferred compensation plan shall continue to be included as
25 regular compensation for the purpose of computing the retirement,
26 pension, or social security contributions made or benefits earned by any
27 employee.
